channel.title: How To Make A Webclient+Jar! (any revision)
channel.description:
this is my tutorial on how to make a webclient for your runescape private server!
Step 1: Download JarMaker by going to http://download.cnet.com/JAR-Maker/3000-2213_4-10588876.html once there click direct download and wait for it to finish downloading :)
Step 2: Extracting JarMaker open what you just downloaded and click extract[IMG]http://i46.tinypic.com/16jrmsm.png[/img]
Step 3: after you do that open up the folder and run the jarmaker.jar [IMG]http://i46.tinypic.com/2qwg8rq.png[/img]
Step 4: for output directory click ... and then go to your desktop and click ok. for output jar file just put "client.jar" for input directory go to your client files. now this can go a few ways: if you see this:[IMG]http://i49.tinypic.com/k98lnc.png[/img] then just click bin then ok. if you open it and you see a folder like this:[IMG]http://i46.tinypic.com/yf6vc.png[/img] then click ok. if you see anything else post a comment or message me and i will add it. after you do that go to manifest template and on the top box type in client (no caps) or if you have a Loader.java file and not client.java just type in Loader (L needs to be cap) Now just click create Jar and wait for it to finish!
Step 5: go to your desktop and look for something that says client with a java symbol:[IMG]http://i50.tinypic.com/2dbkn0h.png[/img]
and double click it to make sure its working. after that go back to your jarmaker and go to the tab that says "JAR signer" for output directory click ... then go to your desktop and click ok. now go to jarsigner location and click ... then go to your c:/ drive and double click program files. after that double click java and then the jdk you use then just double click bin and once there look for jarsigner.exe and double click it.
Step 6: click generate keystore and for the keytool location click ... and you should be in the correct location so just look for "keytool.exe" and double click it. for output keystore file click ... then go to your desktop and for file name type in Certificate and click ok. for keystore alias just put in your name and for public and private key you can put anything, i put 121212 for both.
the rest you can leave and it should look like this when you're done:[IMG]http://i49.tinypic.com/ephtvd.png[/img] then just click generate and then click ... on keystore file and you should be in the right place so just click ok, then for keystore alias put your name and for the keys put what you put while making the keystore. click sign jar and you're almost done!
Step 7: upload your client.jar to somewhere (dropbox is best :P) and while its uploading go to www.webs.com and make an account. do whatever you want when making the website but for pages only check "home". now click "Create my website" and it will take you to the website builder! now near the bottom it has something that says General Layout Social etc.. click layout and then take custom html and drag it onto your page. double click it and for the html code put in :
<applet name="ServerName" width="765" height="503" archive="download link" code="your .class file"> <param name="java_arguments" value="-Xmx256m"> </applet>
for your .class file it is either client.class or Loader.class and for for the download link put the download link.. and for ServerName put your server name. now where it says Xmx256m put what your server says in the run so if you edit your run it should look something like this: [IMG]http://i48.tinypic.com/wjul40.png[/img]
what i circled in red is what you look for in your run for the client and thats what you put instead of Xmx256m
Step 8 after you put your new html code into webs .com click save changes and publish and then you have a webclient!!
please comment or message me if you have any issues- skype name t.rsps- email is tallavi@live.com, Good Luck!
